# Implementation Plan (Updated)

## Project Structure
```
extension/
├── manifest.json
├── background.js
├── popup/
│   ├── popup.html
│   └── popup.js
└── content/
    ├── content.js
    ├── transcript.js
    ├── injector.js
    ├── injected.js
    ├── translate.js      ← not yet implemented
    └── sidebar.js        ← not yet implemented
```

---

## 1. `manifest.json`
- Manifest V2
- Permissions: `storage`, `activeTab`, `tabs`, `http://localhost:5000/*`
  - `tabs` added to support per-tab state management in `background.js`
- Two content script entries:
  - `injector.js` runs at `document_start` to inject `injected.js` before YouTube's scripts run
  - `transcript.js` + `content.js` run at `document_idle`
- `web_accessible_resources: ["content/injected.js"]` — required so `injector.js` can load `injected.js` as a `<script src>` tag, bypassing YouTube's CSP which blocks inline scripts

---

## 2. `background.js`
- Initialises `browser.storage.local` with `{ sourceLang: "de", targetLang: "en" }`
  - `enabled` removed from storage — replaced with per-tab in-memory state (see below)
- Manages per-tab `enabled` state in a `tabStates` object in memory
  - Reason: a single global `enabled` flag affected all tabs simultaneously, which was undesirable
  - Tab state is discarded when the tab is closed via `browser.tabs.onRemoved`
- Responds to `GET_STATE` and `SET_STATE` messages using `sender.tab.id` to identify the tab

---

## 3. `popup.html` / `popup.js`
- Single toggle button showing current state (On/Off)
- Reads and writes per-tab state via `GET_STATE`/`SET_STATE` messages to `background.js`
- On toggle: sends `TOGGLE` message to the active tab's content script so it can react immediately without a page reload
- Uses `browser.tabs.query` to identify the current tab

---

## 4. `injector.js` ← new file
- Runs at `document_start`
- Creates a `<script src="...injected.js">` element pointing to the extension file
- This approach is necessary because YouTube's CSP (`require-trusted-types-for 'script'`) blocks setting `script.textContent` directly
- Removes the script tag after it loads

---

## 5. `injected.js` ← new file
- Runs in page context (not content script context) — this is critical because content scripts have an isolated `window` and cannot access `ytInitialPlayerResponse` or intercept `window.fetch`
- Maintains a `currentTracks` variable updated by listening to `yt-page-data-fetched`
  - Reason: `ytInitialPlayerResponse` does not update on SPA navigation, so it cannot be used to detect the current video's language. `yt-page-data-fetched` fires on every navigation with fresh `playerResponse` data
- Wraps `window.fetch` to intercept calls to `get_panel` — this is the endpoint YouTube's own transcript panel uses
  - Reason: YouTube's `timedtext` API returns empty responses even with valid URLs and credentials. The `get_panel` endpoint is what actually works
- On interception: posts a `YT_TRANSCRIPT_DATA` message to the content script via `window.postMessage` with the data and current language tracks
- Also listens for `yt-navigate-finish` and posts `YT_NAVIGATED` to signal the content script to reset stale data

---

## 6. `transcript.js`
- Listens for `window.postMessage` events from `injected.js`
- On `YT_NAVIGATED`: resets `_transcriptData` and `_currentVideoId` to prevent stale data being used on the next video
- On `YT_TRANSCRIPT_DATA`: checks `event.data.tracks` for `"de"` before storing
  - Reason: `ytInitialPlayerResponse` is not accessible in content script context, so language info is passed from `injected.js` via the message payload
  - If no German track: logs and ignores the data
- `fetchTranscript()` is now synchronous — it reads from `_transcriptData` immediately rather than polling or using a timeout
  - Reason: transcript data is only set after the user opens the transcript panel, so by the time `fetchTranscript()` is called the data is already available
- Parses segments from `transcriptSegmentViewModel.simpleText` and `timestamp` fields
- Returns `{ segments: [{ timestamp, text }] }` or `{ error: string }`
- `resetTranscriptData()` exported for `content.js` to call on navigation

---

## 7. `content.js`
- On `yt-navigate-finish` and initial load: checks for `/watch` page, calls `resetTranscriptData()`
- Listens for `YT_TRANSCRIPT_DATA` messages — this is the trigger for transcript processing, not page navigation
  - Reason: we don't know when the user will open the transcript panel, so we react to the data arriving rather than polling
- Calls `fetchTranscript()` with a 50ms delay after receiving transcript data to ensure `transcript.js` message handler runs first
- Listens for `TOGGLE` messages from popup to update state at runtime

---

## 8. `translate.js` ← not yet implemented
- Will accept array of `{ timestamp, text }`
- For each segment, POST to `http://localhost:5000/translate`:
  ```json
  { "q": "...", "source": "de", "target": "en", "format": "text" }
  ```
- Returns array of `{ timestamp, original, translated }`
- Requests sequential to avoid overwhelming local LibreTranslate
- Failed segments set `translated` to `"[translation error]"`
- `source`/`target` read from `browser.storage.local` as hook for future user-selectable language

---

## 9. `sidebar.js` ← not yet implemented
- Injects `div#yt-translator-sidebar` into YouTube page DOM
- Single scrollable column, each segment pair rendered as:
  ```
  [MM:SS] 🇩🇪  <original text>
  [MM:SS] 🇬🇧  <translated text>
  ```
- Toggle button injected on page + popup both control visibility
- Styled to not clash with YouTube dark/light theme
- Renders progressively as translations arrive rather than waiting for all segments

---

## Key Constraints & Gotchas
1. **YouTube is a SPA** — `yt-navigate-finish` must be used, not just `DOMContentLoaded`
2. **Content script `window` is isolated** — `ytInitialPlayerResponse`, `window.fetch`, and YouTube events are only accessible from `injected.js` which runs in page context
3. **YouTube CSP** — inline scripts are blocked; `injected.js` must be loaded via `<script src>` from `web_accessible_resources`
4. **`ytInitialPlayerResponse` does not update on SPA navigation** — `yt-page-data-fetched` must be used instead for reliable language detection
5. **`timedtext` API returns empty responses** — `get_panel` interception is the only reliable transcript source found
6. **LibreTranslate must have `de` language pack installed** — verify at `http://localhost:5000/languages`
7. **MV2 `browser.*` API** — do not use `chrome.*` anywhere
8. **Translation is slow** — sidebar must show loading state and render progressively

---

## Out of Scope (Future)
- User-selectable source/target language (storage keys already in place in `background.js`)
- Handling multiple transcript languages on one video
- Caching translations to avoid re-fetching on revisit
- Auto-opening the transcript panel (currently requires manual user action)